page.title: 04Telscombe Village
page.content: Telscombe is a very small quiet village.It has a small Saxon church which is called the church of St. Lawrence.The wooden church door has lots of delicate engraving on it. The rector since 1976 has been the Rev. J.G. Holmes.They have no shops in the village. There are some old gas street lamps which have now got light bulbs. There is one farm that keeps horses,sheep, and pigs. Outside the village the road is very bumpy so not a lot of people drive on it as it is not made up. There is an old school house with a sign on it.The old school is not used as a school anymore.The oak cottage is very old.It is covered in grass and weeds and the garden is over grown. Deborah Guyton age 9
